description: Measure the internal supply voltage rail of the control module to check if there is a brief voltage drop every 20 seconds, indicating a possible intermittent power or decoupling issue inside the control module circuitry., outcome='The voltage measurements show nominal values at the Control Input Cables, with ctrl_cable_in_pos at ~11.99\u202fV and ctrl_cable_in_neg near 0\u202fV. No polarity inversion is detected between positive and negative cables. Measurement at the output cables (ctrl_cable_out_pos and ctrl_cable_out_neg) shows low voltage, and no brief voltage drops were observed during the readings.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=200.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> control module relay (during lamp cycling),
description: Visually observe the relay operation inside the control module while the lamp is cycling off/on, to determine if its action (mechanical movement or LED indicator, if present) aligns with the lamp interruption every 20 seconds., outcome='The Control Relay is closed and shows no internal fault, while the Main Load (lamp) is not lit and also has no internal fault detectable by visual inspection. There is no indication of a polarity inversion based on the available information.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> connections between control and load module,
description: Visually inspect the cable connections and fast-connection terminals between the control module and load module for signs of intermittent contact, wear, or looseness that may be causing the lamp to cycle off and on., outcome='All inspected cables—Control Output Cable (+), Control Output Cable (−), Load Input Cable (+), and Load Input Cable (−)—show no observable internal faults, signs of wear, looseness, or intermittent contact. No polarity inversion was detected based on the observed connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
